## {{ rule.title }}

The total allowed Foreign Tax Credit on [Form 1116](https://www.irs.gov/forms-pubs/about-form-1116) line 33 (and Schedule 3 line 1) is the baseline credit under [§ 901](https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=granuleid:USC-prelim-title26-section901&num=0&edition=prelim) / [§ 904](https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=granuleid:USC-prelim-title26-section904&num=0&edition=prelim) plus the [Pub. 514](https://www.irs.gov/publications/p514) worksheet line 21 treaty re-sourcing add-on, reconciled under [DBA-USA Art. 23](https://www.irs.gov/pub/irs-trty/germtech.pdf). This stage promotes the post-treaty sum to a top-level rule-graph fact so every downstream renderer reads a fingerprinted, audited value rather than recomputing the addition outside the graph.

{% set base = rule.inputs_by_key["us.stage.baseline_allowed_ftc"].value | from_json -%}
{% set add = rule.inputs_by_key["us.stage.treaty_additional_ftc"].value | from_json -%}
{% set allowed = rule.inputs_by_key["us.stage.allowed_ftc"].value | from_json -%}
{% set out = rule.outputs[0].value | from_json -%}
For 2025:

- Baseline allowed FTC from US25-14 (lesser of available foreign tax and [§ 904](https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=granuleid:USC-prelim-title26-section904&num=0&edition=prelim) limit, summed across baskets): **{{ base.total_allowed_ftc_usd | money(currency="USD") }}**
- Treaty re-sourcing additional FTC from US25-18 ([Pub. 514](https://www.irs.gov/publications/p514) worksheet line 21, capped by [Form 1116](https://www.irs.gov/forms-pubs/about-form-1116) line 33): **{{ add.treaty_resourcing_additional_ftc_usd | money(currency="USD") }}**
- US25-19 reconciled value (must equal the promoted sum): **{{ allowed.total_allowed_ftc_after_treaty_resourcing_usd | money(currency="USD") }}**
- **Promoted post-treaty allowed FTC ([Form 1116](https://www.irs.gov/forms-pubs/about-form-1116) line 33):** **{{ out.total_allowed_ftc_after_treaty_resourcing_usd | money(currency="USD") }}**

This is the value the orchestrator (`tax_pipeline/pipelines/y2025/us_model.py`) reads from the rule-graph's final facts; the Schedule 3 line 1 / Form 1040 line 20 entries flow from this stage's fingerprinted output.

